---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
---

<section id="about" class="py-20 border-t border-white/5">
  <div
    class="max-w-6xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center"
  >
    <div class="relative group">
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-tr from-primary to-secondary rounded-2xl blur-lg opacity-50 group-hover:opacity-75 transition-opacity duration-500 -z-10"
      >
      </div>

      <div
        class="aspect-square rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-dark-800 border border-white/10 relative"
      >
        <img
          src="/profile.webp"
          alt="Carlos Pérez"
          class="w-full h-full object-cover grayscale group-hover:grayscale-0 transition-all duration-500"
          *
          Si
          no
          tienes
          foto
          aún,
          esto
          mostrará
          un
          cuadro
          gris
          elegante
          *
          onerror="this.style.display='none'"
        />
        <div
          class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center text-dark-200 font-mono text-xs"
        >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-dark-100 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="text-primary">04.</span> About Me
      </h2>

      <div
        class="prose prose-invert prose-p:text-dark-200 text-lg leading-relaxed space-y-4"
      >
        <p>
          Hello! I'm <strong class="text-primary">Carlos Pérez</strong>, a
          Systems Engineering student currently in my 9th semester at
          Universidad Cooperativa de Colombia. Based in Montería, I have
          developed a strong passion for building scalable software solutions.
        </p>

        <p>
          My journey started with a curiosity for how things work, which led me
          to specialize in Full Stack Development. I enjoy the challenge of
          designing robust RESTful APIs and creating intuitive user interfaces.
        </p>

        <p>
          When I'm not coding, you can usually find me watching e-sports
          tournaments especially League of Legends, Valorant, and CS2 or
          listening to music. I enjoy the competitive atmosphere and strategy
          behind each game, which often inspires my creativity as a developer.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-8 font-mono text-sm text-dark-200">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:map-pin" class="text-primary" />
          Montería, Colombia
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:languages" class="text-primary" />
          Spanish (Native)
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:graduation-cap" class="text-primary" />
          Systems Engineer (In Progress)
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
          <Icon name="lucide:gamepad-2" class="text-primary" />
          E-sports Enthusiast
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
